data.text:
Cape Town, South Africa

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: -33.918861, 18.423300.

Cape Town is one of the largest and most crowded cities in modern South Africa, as well as one of the capital cities. Located on the southwestern coast of South Africa, Cape Town is a known port and commercial hub, the key point of the cultural and educational life of the country. It is one of the most popular tourist destinations in South Africa which is visited by thousands of tourists on an annual basis.

With many years of being inhabited and developed as a modern community, the city has great historical and political importance and plays the role of the main economic and trade center of the whole continent. Due to its advanced infrastructure and a great number of tourist attractions, Cape Town is a destination for those who are looking for active time spending, as well as for seaside vacation fans from around the world. There are plenty of wonderful beaches and resorts located in and near the city.

Cape Town is known as one of the oldest cities in the country, and it is an important business center. There are plenty of small and medium companies operating in various spheres located in the city. In the last decade, the city of Cape Town has repeatedly been named the world capital of design in plenty of aspects, starting from IT design and ending up with fashion design.
